{"legislative_session": "20252026", "identifier": "AB1587", "title": "Prescription drug refills: prescriber notifications.", "from_organization": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["bill"], "subject": ["Prescriptiondrugrefills", "prescribernotifications"], "abstracts": [{"note": "summary", "abstract": "Existing law, the Pharmacy Law, provides for the licensure and regulation of pharmacists by the California State Board of Pharmacy. Existing law authorizes a pharmacist to, among other things, perform certain procedures or functions and furnish specified drugs. Existing law authorizes the refilling of a prescription for a dangerous drug without the authorization of the prescriber if the prescriber is unavailable to authorize the refill and, in the pharmacist's professional judgment, failure to refill the prescription might interrupt the patient's ongoing care and have a significant adverse effect on the patient's well-being. Existing law requires a pharmacist to notify the prescriber, as specified, of any prescription refilled without their authorization.\n\nThis bill would only require a pharmacist to provide that notification if a prescriber is identified."}], "other_titles": [{"note": "", "title": "Prescription drugs for life-threatening conditions."}], "other_identifiers": [{"identifier": "ocd-bill-ca-20252026-ab1587"}], "actions": [{"description": "Read first time. To print.", "date": "2026-01-15", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["reading-1"], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "From printer. May be heard in committee February 15.", "date": "2026-01-16", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": [], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "Referred to Com. on B. & P.", "date": "2026-02-02", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["referral-committee"], "related_entities": [{"name": "Com. on B. & P.", "entity_type": "organization", 